abstract = {Key factors that influence variability of the ice-ocean boundary layer are presented. Heat and salt balance at the ice-ocean interface, as well as interaction with the atmosphere, determine changes in the buoyancy flux in the boundary layer. Ice-ocean ablation and freezing are described for sea ice and ice shelves. Spatial differences in the boundary layer under sea ice are also considered, describing typical features of the Arctic Ocean and the Southern Ocean: winter and summer leads, melt ponds, platelet sea ice.},
